review_text: Beautiful park nicely located in the heart of Outremont. The small lake and the fountain give it a nice ambiance, and the large trees provide several shaded areas for the sunny days. There is also a small fenced playground for kids to stretch out.

Clean park. Playground for kids. There's also a small artificial lake and a veteran's memorial for WW1 and WW2. It can get crowded when the weather's nice. The public rest rooms are not always reliable tho. Especially during this covid era.
